{{use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = MEX | NOCname = [[Mexican Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1968 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.com.org.mx }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = [[Mexico City]] | competitors = 275 (233 men and 42 women) | sports = 20 | flagbearer = [[David Bárcena]] | rank = 15 | gold = 3 | silver = 3 | bronze = 3 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1900 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Mexico]]''' was the host nation for the '''[[1968 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Mexico City]]. 275 competitors, 233 men and 42 women, took part in 146 events in 20 sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/MEX/summer/1968/ |title=Mexico at the 1968 Mexico City Summer Games |accessdate=7 September 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>
==Medalists== Mexico won a total of 9 medals (3 of each) which is to date the fewest number of medals won by a host nation at a Summer Olympics.
=== Gold=== * [[Ricardo Delgado (boxer)|Ricardo Delgado]] &mdash; Boxing, Men's Flyweight * [[Antonio Roldán]] &mdash; Boxing, Men's Featherweight * [[Felipe Muñoz]] &mdash; Swimming, Men's 200m Breaststroke
=== Silver=== * [[José Pedraza (racewalker)|José Pedraza]] &mdash; Athletics, Men's 20&nbsp;km Walk * [[Alvaro Gaxiola]] &mdash; Diving, Men's Platform * [[Pilar Roldán]] &mdash; Fencing, Women's Foil
=== Bronze=== * [[Agustín Zaragoza]] &mdash; Boxing, Men's Middleweight * [[Joaquín Rocha]] &mdash; Boxing, Men's Heavyweight * [[Maria Teresa Ramírez]] &mdash; Swimming, Women's 800m Freestyle
